content:
I believe there were two calls in the last days. Monday night was where Chelsea Clinton spoke. I found media reports saying there were over 120k people on this call. 
The other call was already last Tuesday with about 200k women joining.

https://www.cbsnews.com/news/kamala-harris-grassroots-organizers-raise-millions-online-campaign-first-week/
These are just impressive numbers, aren't they?

Thank you!  I was on both calls.  Perhaps the speakers WERE talking about two different calls.  I stayed on later than I thought I would to hear Chelsea Clinton.  The numbers of attendees, the $$$s raised, the NEW voter registrations (especiallly from young people) ... it's all amazing.  I have so much hope and confidence that we can get it right this time.
